abstract: Great Britain's House of Lords votes to delay proposal by conservative government of British Prime Min David Cameron, which included plan to decrease cash benefits offered to citizens in low-paying jobs; unelected chamber, which traditionally does not block but can stall measures, had been alarmed by consequences of government's latest round of spending cuts.
lead_paragraph: The House of Lords voted to delay the latest round of spending cuts proposed by Prime Minister David Cameron, which involve decreasing a cash benefit for people in low-paying jobs.

headline.main: Unelected Chamber in Britain Delays Cameron’s Spending Cuts
headline.print_headline: Unelected Chamber Delays Cameron’s Spending Cuts
